# Conventional Commits

## Required Format
```
<type>(<scope>): <short summary>

<body>
```

- **Line 1** (`subject`): type + scope + summary, up to 72 characters
- **Line 2**: blank (required)
- **Line 3+** (`body`): full description of what was done and why

## Language
Commits are always in **English** — subject and body.

---

## Allowed Types
| Type | When to use |
|------|--------------|
| `feat` | New feature |
| `fix` | Bug fix |
| `test` | Add or fix tests |
| `refactor` | Refactor without behavior change |
| `chore` | Config, build, dependencies |
| `docs` | Documentation (README, comments) |
| `style` | Formatting, lint (no logic change) |
| `perf` | Performance improvement |
| `ci` | CI/CD pipelines |

## Suggested Scopes
`cli`, `core`, `steps`, `templates`, `utils`, `bin`, `config`, `tests` — adjust to the project.

---

## Examples

### feat with body
```
feat(steps): add generate step to copy base template

Copy templates/base into targetDir with project name substitution.
Uses utils/fs; runner invokes step after init and before install.
```

### fix with body
```
fix(core): return clear error when targetDir is missing

Runner now throws with a user-friendly message instead of a generic
exception so users know exactly what to provide.
```

### test with body
```
test(utils): add unit tests for exec and fs

Cover: exec success/failure, fs copy/write/mkdir/exists.
All side effects mocked; no real filesystem or shell.
```

### chore with body
```
chore(config): add ESLint and Prettier

Add .eslintrc.json with @typescript-eslint/recommended and prettier.
Add .prettierrc with singleQuote, printWidth 100, trailingComma all.
Scripts: lint, lint:fix, format.
```

---

## Rules
- NEVER use `git commit -m "quick fix"` or vague messages.
- NEVER omit the body — every code change requires a description.
- The body explains **what** and **why**, not **how**.
- Breaking changes: add `BREAKING CHANGE:` at the end of the body.
- Reference issues when present: `Closes #12` at the end of the body.
- NEVER add `Co-authored-by: Cursor` or AI co-authorship in commits.
